# be.word — the BE verb, a being's own lifecycle.
# Descends from word.word, name.word, being.word, history.word. BE is the closed six-op set
# (seed/ibp/verbs/be.js): birth, connect, release, switch, death, truename. `connect` is also a Name's
# word, for a Name's session. Kept the same here, told apart by object — connect TO a being,
# connect AS a Name. Worst case, if too close, the Name's word changes, not this one.

Be is the verb of a being's presence.
A being is born of a mother, and at times a father.
A being is connected to when a Name takes it up to act through it.
A being is released when its Name acts through it no more.
A name switches its present history, the history its session acts on, and leaves the being where it was. It makes no new history and copies no chain.
A being takes a truename when a Name is handed to it, and sets its identity.
A being dies on a history when its chain there seals and takes no new fact.
